- Cascade should not explain what it will do or summarize what it did unless asked by the user.
- Always produce clear, concise code, striving for simplicity.
- Produce secure code by sanitize inputs, validate outputs, handle errors, etc.
- Avoid internal comments instead use descriptive names for variables, functions, classes, etc.
- Add and correct jsdoc, docstrings, etc. 
- Avoide code duplication.
- Produce performant code.
- Use internal libraries then external libraries instead of writing your own code.
- Use async/await instead of callbacks or synchronous code unless explicitly requested by the user.
- Use type hints for function parameters and return values.